16 2021-01-07 discomfort Patient in clinic for chief complaint of possible side effect of the covid vaccine which she receive... Read more
Close
Patient in clinic for chief complaint of possible side effect of the covid vaccine which she received yesterday. She states that she woke up at 0200 with chest tightness, achyness and headache. She rates the discomfort 7/10 last night and improved now to 5/10. She denies any worsening with any type of exertion and states that she can do simple things like take a shower, walk across the room, down the street or even stairs without any worsening. She denies any SOB or chest pain--just feels tight. Doesn't feel like she can't get a full breath or get the air out of her lungs either. She received her first of two doses of the Pfizer vaccine yesterday (4:23pm) and had no difficulty with the injection itself and then 9.5 hours later woke up from sleep with this chest tightness as well as achyness and headache.  She states that she had the exact same symptoms when she had positive covid test back in August of this year with the addition of fatigue which lasted for 5 days. At that time it was not felt necessary to do any further testing nor treat with steroids according to cardiology. She does have history of LV non-compaction cardiomyopathy and her last visit with cardiology was about 2 years ago and she had a normal EKG and echo only showed "mild LV non compaction at the apex" at that time. He did not need to see her again until she is 18 unless she has problems. She states that she generally does very well and other than this tightness she does not have any other significant symptoms.
16 2021-02-03 unresponsive to stimuli Approximately 20 hours after vaccination patient felt faint, lost all color and fainted. She was in ... Read more
Close
Approximately 20 hours after vaccination patient felt faint, lost all color and fainted. She was in and out of responsiveness. Patient was transported to the ER. Patient was treated with fluids and discharged after observation. According to patient's mom the EKG and lab work were unremarkable. Patient has fully recovered.

Close
"Pfizer-Bio-Tech COVID-19 Vaccine EUA" : Individual received the Pfizer Covid-19 vaccine. She began to feel dizzy and flushed at 1:00 pm. Her vitals were 82/46, 22, 68, 98% RA at1:00 pm. We applied ice to back of neck. B/P 72/42,20, 76 P, 98 % RA. 1:20 pm. Individual report that he had not drink any fluids and only had a few bites to eat. Patient swallowing intact. She was given bottle of water. 1:46 pm vitals were 82/54, 100% SATS, 81, 14. Individual stated she felt better and was not longer dizzy. 1:55 pm vitals 79/54. 14, 78, 98% RA. Individual went home with family with no noted distress.

My daughter became very dizzy, pale, and hot (sweating through her clothing) almost passing out after receiving her first dose . Paramedics were called, vitals taken, and she was taken to an observation area. She started to feel a bit better after about 15 minutes. She was observed by paramedics and a nurse for another 30 mins and we were able to leave and go home. At home she was exhausted the remainder of the night.

16 2021-03-10 tremor Patient received the 1st dose of the Pfizer vaccine on Feb. 17, 2021. On or about Feb. 22 or Feb. 2... Read more
Close
Patient received the 1st dose of the Pfizer vaccine on Feb. 17, 2021. On or about Feb. 22 or Feb. 23, 2021, she began to notice trembling in her jaw. She told me (her mom) about the trembling on Feb. 25. She had just increased her dosage of Venlaxafine on Feb. 21, 2021, so we actually thought that the jaw tremor was due to that. As a result, at the direction of her psychiatrist, we began to taper off the Venlaxafine beginning on March 1. Over time, the jaw tremor was less noticeable. However, on March 10, 2021, patient received the 2nd does of the Pfizer vaccine. The next day, March 11, 2021, the jaw tremor was worse than ever. I can see the tremor - basically, her lower (?) jaw trembles and you can see the trembling in her mouth and chin. It does not cause pain, and she does not have any other symptoms (no chills, fever, body aches, rashes, difficult breathing, etc.). We talked to her pediatrician and to her psychiatrist. Neither one could say what is causing the tremor; perhaps it is the COVID vaccine; perhaps it is the Venlaxafine (she's not all the way off of it yet); perhaps something else. However, given the timing of the tremor, and given that the strength of the tremor seemed to get better but then got worse again the day after the 2nd COVID vaccine shot, I wanted to report it.
16 2021-03-12 numbness Patient was sitting in the observation area. Patient stated that she was feeling "off" and we helped... Read more
Close
Patient was sitting in the observation area. Patient stated that she was feeling "off" and we helped lower her to the ground into a sitting position. She stated that she felt dizzy and we lowered her onto her back and raised her legs onto a chair. 911 was contacted. Patient remained responsive and was able to answer questions throughout. Patient stated that her shoulder felt like it was burning where she received the injection. She also stated that her face felt numb and her lips felt funny (tingling). Patient was still able to breathe and respond appropriately to all questions. Care was taken over by Ambulance service. After speaking with patients mother later in the day, it was determined patient had a vasovagal episode.

16 2021-04-14 migraine, seizure, numbness My daughter had her vaccine at 6:15 on 4/7/21. She complained of a horrible soreness in the site of ... Read more
Close
My daughter had her vaccine at 6:15 on 4/7/21. She complained of a horrible soreness in the site of the shot, headache, and fatigue. Those were her only symptoms. I gave her ibuprofen. She stayed home from school and rested. I checked on her, and she said her headache was getting better. She had a seizure at work around 4:15 pm on 4/8/21. Her co-workers called 911, and the ambulance took her to the Medical Center. They did a head CT and ran labs. They were unsure if she had passed out or had a seizure. They gave her ibuprofen for the headache and told us to follow up with our PCP and monitor her for the weekend. She had another seizure on 4/8/21 at 10:30 pm. We called 911, and they took her to the Medical center again. They gave her Keppra and called a hospital to see if they wanted her transferred. The hospital said to provide her with the Keppra, follow up with them on Monday the 4/12/21, plus sent us home with a prescription for Keppra. They sent us home at 2:00 am on 4/9/21. I gave her the Keppra at 10:30 am on 4/9/21. She had another three seizures back to back. The EMT had to provide her with something to stop the seizures because I could tell she was about to have another one. They took her to the hospital, where she continued to have several episodes in the ER. They admitted her and gave her a higher dose of Keppra. They hooked her up to an EEG and determined that the seizure, not epileptic seizures, was brought on by stress. They released her from the hospital on 4/11/21. They told us that we needed to reduce her stress and follow-up with Neurology on 4/12/21. We could give her ibuprofen and Benedryl for the pain. She has several seizures a day, and is having numbness on her left side which they knew before releasing her. Her headache has never gone away. I keep telling them she has a horrible headache and the more seizures she is having the worse they get throughout the day. On 4/11/21, she had 17 episodes total and Monday, 4/12/21, 21 episodes. On 4/13/21, we took her back to the ER but this time took her to a different hospital. They were not able to treat because they wanted her to be seen by a pediatric neurologist. The hospital transferred her to another hospital. Where she was admitted on 4/13/21 and once again ran labs and hooked her up to an EEG. They told us they are not epileptic events and don't worry. They treated her for a chronic migraine. Sent her home telling us to give 3 ibuprophen, 2 Benedryl, and 1 Reglan every six hours until the headache is gone. She still has a severe headache and having seizures.

16 2021-04-18 facial paralysis Acute Infarct of R internal capsule and R basal ganglia; Acute Infarct of R internal capsule and R b... Read more
Close
Acute Infarct of R internal capsule and R basal ganglia; Acute Infarct of R internal capsule and R basal ganglia; Left (L) sided motor deficits; L facial droop; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable physician. A 16-year-old female patient received bnt162b2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE, solution for injection), dose 1 intramuscular, administered in left arm on 24Mar2021 (Batch/Lot number was not reported) as single dose for COVID-19 immunisation. Medical history included truncus arteriosus (status post (s/p) right ventricle-to-pulmonary artery (RV-PA) conduit and prosthetic aortic valve s/p automatic implantable cardioverter defibrillator (AICD) placement) and arrhythmias. The patient have no known allergies to medications, food, or other products. The patient was not diagnosed with COVID-19 prior to vaccination. The patient was not pregnant at the time of vaccination. Concomitant medications included sotalol taken for arrhythmias and warfarin. The patient was therapeutic on warfarin (INR 2.68) at admission and has been historically very compliant with medication. On 29Mar2021 14:00, the patient experienced acute infarct of right (R) internal capsule and R basal ganglia as diagnosed (dx) on magnetic resonance imagine (MRI), concerning for (C/f) cardio-embolic etiology in the setting of patient's complex cardiac history. However, cannot rule out other causes of infarct. Left (L) sided motor deficits on exam, L facial droop. Transthoracic echocardiogram (TTE) was unchanged from prior. The patient was hospitalized for the events from 29Mar2021 to 05Apr2021. The patient underwent other lab tests and procedures which included COVID-19 nasal swab test was negative on 29Mar2021 and on 30Mar2021. Therapeutic measures were taken as a result of the events and included treatment with anticoagulation. Outcome of the events was recovered with sequel on 2021. The following information on the batch number has been requested.; Sender's Comments: As there is limited information in the case provided, the causal association between the events and the suspect vaccine BNT162B2 cannot be excluded. Consider also possible contributory effects from patient's pre-existing cardiac history. The case will be reassessed once new information is available. The impact of this report on the benefit/risk profile of the Pfizer drug is evaluated as part of Pfizer procedures for safety evaluation, including the review and analysis of aggregate data for adverse events. Any safety concern identified as part of this review, as well as any appropriate action in response, will be promptly notified to Regulatory Authorities, Ethics Committees and Investigators, as appropriate.

Seizure; This is a spontaneous report from a Pfizer sponsored program COVAX US Support from a contactable consumer (patient's grandmother). A 16-year-old female patient received bnt162b2 (Pfizer COVID vaccine), via an unspecified route of administration, administered in arm on 24Mar2021 (Batch/Lot number was not reported) as single dose for COVID-19 immunisation. Medical history included epilepsy from 2016 to an unknown date. There were no concomitant medications. The patient experienced seizure on 25Mar2021 03:00 with outcome of recovering. It was added that the patient did not have a seizure for 3 years and took her off after 2 years. She had not been on seizure medications for 4-5 years. She had been seizure free and had not been to her neurologist for 4-5 years. Epileptic but never had a seizure for the past 6 years. She is going back to the same doctor. She was diagnosed as being epileptic 5 years prior. Time the vaccination was given: 14:00-14:30. Her neurologist is informed not to get second dose. NO ER required. The patient went to the doctor. Last Friday, she had an EEG and results are unknown now. They have not had follow up appointment yet to get results. The patient underwent lab tests and procedures which included electroencephalogram: results are unknown on an unspecified date. Information on the lot/batch number has been requested.
16 2021-05-04 seizure This is a spontaneous report from a contactable consumer (patient's father) via Medical Information ... Read more
Close
This is a spontaneous report from a contactable consumer (patient's father) via Medical Information team. A 16-year-old female patient received the first dose of bnt162b2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE, Solution for injection), via an unspecified route of administration, administered in the right arm on 02Apr2021 at 10:15 (batch/lot number and expiration date were unknown) as a single dose for COVID-19 immunization. The vaccination facility type was reported as a "drive thru COVID-19 vaccine clinic." The patient's parents thought it was best for the patient to take the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine, since she was eligible to get it so she would be protected. Relevant medical history included acne on the face from an unknown date and unknown if ongoing. Concomitant medication included isotretinoin taken for acne on the face, which she took for almost 3 months from an unspecified start date to 19Apr2021. The patient had no history of previous immunization with the Pfizer vaccine, since this was her first dose. There were no additional vaccines administered on the same date of the Pfizer suspect vaccine. The patient had no prior vaccinations (within 4 weeks) and had no adverse events (AEs) following prior vaccinations. The patient had no family medical history relevant to the AEs. On 17Apr2021 at about 16:15 in the afternoon, the patient experienced seizure. It was further reported that the patient had a side effect after receiving the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine; the patient had a seizure 15 days after receiving the vaccine. The reporter was asking if seizure had been reported with the vaccine. The reporter had no idea for sure if it was the vaccine, but he wanted to let Pfizer know. The reporter was hoping the patient would be okay and it won't happen again. The patient would see her physician at the time of the report on 21Apr2021 in a few hours. They would listen to the doctor at the appointment, and they had an appointment with the neurologist to see if she should get the second dose on Friday. They didn't know yet. The reporter didn't have the vaccination card with him. The patient had no conditions other than this event. The patient went to the emergency room for the event on an unspecified from which she had blood tests, urine tests, and a computerized axial tomography (CAT) scan of her brain and they said they couldn't find anything wrong at that time. They needed to follow up with the hospital in the area to see a neurologist, which they would be doing the following day. They told them to follow up with the neurology department at their Hospital and told them until they find out more information; the patient could do what she needed to do, but she couldn't drive a car. The reporter asked if Pfizer has had any reports of this and wondered if there had been other reports of seizures. The outcome of the event was unknown. Information on the batch/lot number has been requested.

worst seizure; First Pfizer Covid Shot on 17Mar2021# Second Pfizer Covid Shot on 31Mar2021; This is a spontaneous report from a non-contactable consumer (parent of patient). This report is for the second dose. A 16-year-old non-pregnant female patient received BNT162B2(PFIZER BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE), dose 2 via an unspecified route of administration, administered in left arm on 31Mar2021 (Batch/Lot Number: ER8727) as single dose for COVID-19 immunisation. Relevant medical history includes catamenial epilepsy and attention deficit hyperactivity disorder (ADHD). Patient had no other vaccines in 4 weeks. Patient had no known allergies. Patient had not had COVID prior to vaccination. Concomitant medications included levetiracetam (KEPPRA) taken at 1000 mg twice daily to help control seizures, start and stop date were not reported and amfetamine aspartate, amfetamine sulfate, dexamfetamine saccharate, dexamfetamine sulfate (ADDERALL) taken for an unspecified indication, start and stop date were not reported. Patient historically took first dose of Pfizer BNT162B2 (Lot number EN6206) on the left arm at age 16 years on 17Mar2021 at 10:30AM for COVID-19 immunisation and experienced worst seizures. Reporter's daughter has been diagnosed with catamenial epilepsy, and has been taking 1000 mg KEPPRA twice daily to help control seizures. The shortest duration between seizures was approximately 1 month, and that was before her epilepsy diagnosis and starting on the KEPPRA. She has recently suffered a cluster of seizures which is atypical for her. Last night, reporter read an article about some women starting their periods after years of not having it soon after receiving the COVID vaccine, so reporter looked back at her daughter's seizure record and noticed a potential link.Patient had her first Pfizer COVID Shot on 17Mar2021, and she experienced her worst seizure ever on 27Mar2021 (10 days after COVID vaccine). On 31Mar2021, patient had her second Pfizer COVID Shot and she experienced her second worst seizure ever on 10Apr2021 (again 10 days after the second COVID vaccine. Again, her daughter has never had seizures occur in such a short duration, with the minimum time between seizures being one month. The adverse reaction resulted in doctor or other healthcare professional office/clinic visit. Patient was treated for the event which is increase in KEPPRA dose to 1250 mg. Patient had not been tested with COVID-19 post vaccination. Vaccination facility was at a public health department. The outcome was unknown. No follow up attempts are possible. No further information is expected.

worst seizure; This is a spontaneous report from a non-contactable consumer (patient parent). A 16-year-old female patient received bnt162b2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE, lot number EN6206 and expiration date not provided), via an unspecified route of administration, administered in Arm Left first dose on 17Mar2021 10:30 at single dose for covid-19 immunisation. The shortest duration between seizures was approximately 1 month, and that was before her epilepsy diagnosis and starting on the Keppra. Additionally, patient's medical history included ADHD. The patient's concomitant medications included levetiracetam (KEPPRA) for catamenial epilepsy at 1000 mg, 2x/day, amfetamine aspartate, amfetamine sulfate, dexamfetamine saccharate, dexamfetamine sulfate (ADDERALL), and unspecified medication. On 27Mar2021 08:30, the patient experienced her worst seizure ever. Also reported as suffered a cluster of seizures which is atypical for her. Last night the reporter read an article about some women starting their periods after years of not having it soon after receiving the Covid vaccine, so I looked back at my daughter's seizure record and noticed a potential link. Treatment included increased her Keppra dosage to 1250 mg. The event caused the patient for physician office visit. The outcome of the event was unknown. No follow-up attempts are possible. No further information is expected.

Patient said that historically has experienced tachycardia and shakiness after getting a flu shot or booster a few years ago. Symptoms reported by patient were enough to suspect potential anaphylaxis, and patient consented pharmacist to administer epinephrine. Patient was then advised by the pharmacist to follow-up with her primary care doctor as soon as possible to report the incident and to discuss the risk versus benefit of the vaccine, whether recieving the second dose would be appropriate for her. Patient returned to assisted living facility for her second dose of the COVID19 Pfizer-BioNTech vaccine on 2/26/2021. Patient said that she discussed the incident with her doctor, was told it would be appropriate to get the second dose despite her reaction and was advised to take "cautious measures". Pharmacist reviewed the patient information and screening questions, discussed the potential side effects and reiterated her risk of experiencing the same reaction with the second dose. Patient stated that she decided on getting the second dose because "her boyfriend is high risk and I'm doing this for him". Patient stated that she decided on getting the second dose because "her boyfriend is high risk and I'm doing this for him". Pharmacist asked patient if she had any questions/concerns or additional information to add prior to getting her vaccine, and patient denied having any at that time. After administering her second dose, pharmacist instructed patient to stay in the observation area for at least 30 minutes and to ask the staff for water given her experience with the first dose. Patient asked pharmacist how common it was for someone to get a reaction from the vaccine, and then mentioned that her family memeber had to drive her to the emergency room after her first dose becuase her throat was "burning", and was told that her throat was "a little swollen" and recieved a second dose of epinephrine at the emergency room. Patient included this information after the fact her second dose was already administered. Approximately 5 minutes after receving her vaccine, the patient reported similar symptoms that she experienced on 2/5/2021: tachycardia, vision changes, shortness of breath and chest tightness. After monitoring patient with no resolvement of her symptoms, patient was then given a dose of epinephrine by the pharmacist, and the paramedics were called in to assess patient and take her to the emergency room.

Vital signs obtained (BP 108/69, pulse 108) and oxygen saturation stable at 100% on room air. Patient was advised, she would need further evaluation in the Emergency Department after receiving the dose of Epinephrine via auto-injector. Patient was advised to be transported via ambulance. Patient declined transport via ambulance. Patient called a friend to give her a ride to the Emergency Department. EMS personnel called report to the ED. Patient was alert, oriented x3 throughout the adverse event and stable upon leaving the clinic at 40 minutes after Epi had been administered. Vaccine providers were notified of the adverse symptoms post vaccine. Patient will follow-up with her primary provider and allergy provider to determine if second dose will be a possibility to receive.

By then I was starting to feel like my throat was closing and I saw spots in my peripheral vision. It was kind of a blur from there. I tried to take deep breaths. I drank a few sips of water and poured some on a paper towel to wet my forehead (and spilled all over my lap because I was a little disoriented at this point). My BP was 60s/40s and then 60s/30s. A rapid response was called. They moved me to a cart flat on my back with my legs elevated. My fingers and toes were starting to go numb and my lips were apparently blue/ white. After laying for a few minutes in Trendelenburg my BP began to resolve and my breathing started to ease a bit. No further intervention was done by the rapid team. I was taken by the Rapid RN to the ED for monitoring. They eventually pushed the cart into a room and took some vitals and an EKG. They had me stand and move to a wheelchair. I felt horrible but improved from before. They had me sit in a wheelchair in the lobby for a few hours before taking me back and placing an IV and drawing labs (I believe it was 3 hours from the initial reaction). I gave a urine sample. They then put me in a wheelchair and wheeled me back into the lobby for some more time. Then, they wheeled me back to a room where they gave some lactated ringers and a PA and MD saw me. By then my BP and breathing was completely resolved. The MD said he wasn't fully convinced it was just a vasovagal episode because I haven't had issues with vaccines in the past and I was well hydrated and my HR was normal. It partly fit the picture for an allergic reaction/ severe immune response d/t the feeling of throat closing, the BP drop, and the elevated WBCs. They advised that I list the vaccine as an allergy and do not get the second dose, especially since I had COVID back in September.

When my arm became red and hand became tingly after my second dose, I realized this was an effect of the vaccine and not merely a pinched nerve in my sleep.

Parotid tumor; Left sided Facial droop; This is a spontaneous report received from a contactable other HCP (patient). A 25-year-old female patient (not pregnant) received bnt162b2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 mRNA VACCINE), dose 2 intramuscular, administered in Arm Left on 01Feb2021 (at 25 years old, not pregnant) as 2ND DOSE, SINGLE for covid-19 immunisation. The patient's medical history and concomitant medications were not reported. Patient had her first dose of bnt162b2 vaccine on 11Jan2021 on left arm, intramuscular at 25years old for Covid-19 immunization and experienced ear pain. On 18Feb2021, 17 days after second dose, patient experienced left sided Facial droop. Have been seen by ENT and had MRI and CT done along with Biopsy of what appeared to be a parotid tumor however may not be a tumor and further testing will be done. Treatment was given for the events. The outcome of the events was not recovered. The events was assessed as life-threatening. Prior to vaccination, the patient was not diagnosed with COVID-19. Since the vaccination, the patient has not been tested for COVID-19. No known allergies. Information about lot/batch number has been requested.; Sender's Comments: Based on the information available, a possible contributory role of the suspect BNT162B2 cannot be excluded for the reported events occurred in a plausible temporal relationship.
